<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Norrad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I am considering creating a human paladin for Smithing purposes mostly.  I know this may be a bad choice, but what abilities should I increase when I first create the character?  (i.e. "wisdom, int, char")<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Boiler</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">From what I understand for about 400pp any character can do it.  I just read a guide and his paladin with int 75 did it for about 350pp.<P>If you have the money, it makes up for low stats.  Now as far as creating a character.  If it is purely a trade skill character (ie no adventuring) then you want the highest wis/int combo.  I believe erudite enchanter or high-elf enchanter.<P>If you are new to EQ, it costs lots of money to get good at any trade skill. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">faethoran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">i am a mastersmith and it costed me about 125 to 150pp.  not totally sure on the cost because i did not keep track of the prices. but this is just a rough estimate for me.<P>my character is a barbarain shaman.  int of 60.  wisdom of 98.  charisma of 108<P>i bought (2) +2 int rings for smithing only.<BR>also i have a high wisdom so i did not have to buy anything there.<BR>charisma is very important because it lowers the cost of all you supplies overall which is a must.  my base charisma is like 70.  but do to charisma items and the spell spirit of snake i could increase to 108.<P>so overall i do not think it matters what race of character you use.  just make sure that you have access to all the supplies and have good faction.  this also helps a lot too<P>faethoran boneblood<BR>mastersmith<BR>barbarian shaman<BR>brell serilis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Baxt-Quellious</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">To my knowledge, it is INT that guides how FAST someone learns a skill.<P>The others are right, though.  If you put enough money into the skill, you will get to master, regardless of other stats.<P>------------------<BR>AKA:<BR>Tiny Oak-Nameless Server<BR>Aldaen-Prexus Server<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Hydro Jynn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Actually, i have a high elf, who is a master smith, cost me quite a bit of coin, but with an intelligence of 102, str of 106(items increased this), wisdom of 130. I heard rumors that wisdom and str help the sucession of the armor or tool that you are making.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Bazill</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Wisdom is your chance it works<P>Intelegence is the chance the skill gose up<P>So for any crafter the highest wisdom will have the best chance to make the items and the higher the intelegence the faster the skill will go up ...<P>Bazill Wraithbone , master smith , master tailor</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">ciladar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">i dont know about you guys, but im a High elf Paladin I have 92 INT. So far its taken me about 300pp to get my skill up to 86. I dont know why, but learn from my mistakes.  Make everything until its trival.  Dont put more than 10 points into smithing. This way you can make metal bits and gain lvls. Metal bits suck. They are expensive. Over a gp a piece. Every recipe short banded armor, weapons, and a few others require a lot of metal bits. Dont sell your metal bits either.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
